The paper deals with compression algorithms and the Slepian-Wolf theorem, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of Kolmogorov complexity and polynomial time algorithms suggests that the paper may also fall under computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the optimization of parameters, which is a common theme in cryptography (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
